      "strategyParagraphs": [
        "The user strikes a pose with a 30 frame startup. Then, fires a projectile that travels >32 studs in 55 frames before despawning.",
        "After that, you are left in stun for 25 frames on whiff. If the projectile hits, the user will grab the target and perform a barrage of attacks on them, dealing damage.",
        "If the projectile is blocked, the user will get a block endlag of 46f, more than punishable for anyone with half a braincell, so do not use this in neutral."
      ],
      "bulletPoints": [
        "<strong>The Projectile Thingy:</strong> Because the hit detection is tied to a spawned projectile rather than the user's physical body, the move can grab opponents through solid walls, even if the user doesn't move.",
        "<strong>Combo Extender (+48f):</strong> While the attacker leaves their grab animation after 113f, the target is forced to endure a total stun of 161 frames (113f of the animation + 48f of extra stun). This decent frame advantage creates a window to link into any attacks in the kit."
